# --- standard base (project-standard/templates/gitignore) ---
.DS_Store
local/

# Public repositories keep this tracked base minimal so the remote reveals no
# local tooling. The tooling ignores go to .git/info/exclude (a per-clone file
# that is never committed), installed by scripts/apply-standard.sh:
#   backlog/
#   CLAUDE.md
#   CLAUDE.local.md
#   .claude/
#
# Private repositories have no remote to hide from: they track CLAUDE.md (it
# holds the instructions; no AGENTS.md is shipped) and keep the tooling ignores
# here instead:
#   CLAUDE.local.md
#   .claude/
#   # backlog/   (uncomment to keep the task system off the remote)
#
# Language- and tool-specific rules go below this line.
